<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-18T04:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-18T04:41:00-05:00" n="4" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d4">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/3505</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LM1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Langhorne</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-18T11:00:00+01:19">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 4.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>863. Have been informally and confidentially approached by member of
                                British Legation here regarding attitude which Government of the
                                United States intends to adopt towards American citizens of enemy
                                origin whose business transactions may be under suspicion, and
                                regarding possibility that United States will adopt system of black
                                list similar to British. Respectfully ask instructions in
                                premises.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LM1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Langhorne</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>